  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Consecutive patients with a colonoscopy with inadequate bowel preparation, for any
             indication and where the endoscopist considers that the colonoscopy should be repeated
             to optimize the visualization with a better bowel preparation. Participants must have
             been properly informed and they have to sign the inform consent.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Hospitalized patients

          -  Unwillingness to participate in the study

          -  Inability to follow instructions: cognitive impairment or language barrier

          -  Inability to use a telephone or not owning a telephone

          -  Active inflammatory bowel disease

          -  Severe renal impairment

          -  Pregnancy of breast feeding
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
